radiographic_examinations.findings: Normal lung fields with no signs of pneumonia; multiple subtle irregularities involving the bilateral inferior ribs suggestive of inferior rib notching.

Large collateral vessels all over the chest wall with tortuously dilated internal mammary arteries, posterior and anterior intercostal arteries, and large paravertebral and parascapular collateral vessels; complete discontinuity between the aortic arch and descending thoracic aorta with a 1.5 cm gap; distinct outline of the aortic arch interruption with only collateral vessels supplying flow to the distal segment.
